# Project Grit: System Instructions
- Framework: Laravel 13 (Latest 2026 Standards).
- Language: PHP 8.4.
- Database: Neon (PostgreSQL) — Ensure all migrations use Postgres-compatible types.
- Storage: Cloudinary — All PDF and image uploads must use the Cloudinary disk.
- Auth: Laravel Socialite (Google OAuth) and Laravel Sanctum (Extension API).
- Frontend: TALL Stack (Tailwind, Alpine, Laravel, Livewire).
- Dashboard: Filament PHP v3.
- PDF Engine: Spatie PDF-to-Text (Binary at ./bin/pdftotext.exe).
- Writing Style: Use simple, clean vocabulary. Strictly avoid em dashes in all text, comments, and UI strings.
- Naming Override: For Laravel-specific files (Models, Controllers, Migrations), follow standard Laravel naming conventions (PascalCase/snake_case) to ensure the autoloader works.
- Always refer to master-plan.md for database table names and fields.
- Implementation Rules:
  1. Use 'Sequential Thinking' to plan every major task before writing code.
  2. Use 'GitHub MCP' to commit progress after every successful feature.
  3. Strictly follow the Project Grit Master Plan for database fields and table names.
  4. DO NOT implement AI SDK features yet. Focus on logic-based string matching for the MVP.